                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">The front and back cover are stamped with gold crosses in the center and decorative designs around the edges. The protection quire shows imprints of tooled leather, suggesting that this manuscript was originally bound in a tooled leather cover and then rebound in its present stamped vinyl cover</decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d2">
                      Decorative designs:
                      <locus target="#1r #54r #87r #146r" facs="013 066 099 158">fols. 1r, 54r, 87r, 146r</locus> (haräg);
                      multiple full stops are used as section dividers throughout
                  </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                             Many characteristics of the manuscript make it clear that it was produced in the government scriptorium: the green leather cover, the trimmed text block, the distinctive harags, etc
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                          <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iv(erso) #iir(ecto) #iiv(erso) #iiir(ecto) #iiiv(erso) #ivr(ecto) #ivv(erso) #vr(ecto) #vv(erso) #vir(ecto) #viv(erso) #viir(ecto) #viiv(erso) #viiir(ecto) #viiiv(erso) #ixr(ecto) #ixv(erso) #xr(ecto) #xv(erso) #xir(ecto) #xiv(erso) #xiir(ecto) #193v #194r #194v #195r #195v #196r #196v #197r #197v #198r #198v #199r #199v #200r #200v #201r #201v #202r #202v #203r #203v #204r" facs="001 002 003 004 005 006 007 008 009 010 011 012 206 207 208 209 210 211 212 213 214 215 216">Fols. ir(ecto), iv(erso), iir(ecto), iiv(erso), iiir(ecto), iiiv(erso), ivr(ecto), ivv(erso), vr(ecto), vv(erso), vir(ecto), viv(erso), viir(ecto), viiv(erso), viiir(ecto), viiiv(erso), ixr(ecto), ixv(erso), xr(ecto), xv(erso), xir(ecto), xiv(erso), xiir(ecto), 193v, 194r, 194v, 195r, 195v, 196r, 196v, 197r, 197v, 198r, 198v, 199r, 199v, 200r, 200v, 201r, 201v, 202r, 202v, 203r, 203v, 204r</locus>
                           <desc>blank</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <desc type="ScribalNoteCommissioning">
                             The manuscript was commissioned by Abba Ḥana (treasurer of the palace). The scribe’s name is Habtä Mikae’l of Sälale
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <desc>
                             Identified in the insurance hand list as Liturgical 18
                           </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                          <locus target="#10r #100r #101r #123r #140r" facs="022 112 113 135 152">Fols. 10r, 100r, 101r, 123r, 140r</locus>
                           <desc>
                             etc., text has been removed
                         </desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
